726192f-a.title: Queens: Bowne Street - Sanford Avenue
726192f-a.text:
Bowne Street, east side, north from Sanford to 41st Avenues,
showing a row of old mansions.
P. L. Sperr  April 8, 1927
726192f-a.folder: Bowne Street & Sanford Avenue, Queens, NY

727958f-a.title: Queens: Sanford Avenue - Bowne Street
727958f-a.text:
191-213 Sanford Ave., south side, west of Bowne Street (formerly
Milton Street.) The first house in this view is No. 213. The first
three houses were standing in 1873. The Walker Estate owned practically
the whole of the south side of Sanford Ave. between Bowne and Union
Streets.
March 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

727959f-a.title: Queens: Sanford Avenue - Bowne Street
727959f-a.text:
213 Sanford Avenue, at the S.W. corner of Bowne Street,
showing the Walker house. George, John, a nd Mary Walker were
the owners ahout 1873. Another owner was Jos. Dykes.
1922
